Items.Name: NFI||75049|Testing Financial Detail Report to Smartsheet
Items.Description:
After  changing the 3 integrations to add new colums (US#76856), Unit Testing efforts should be between EBS - OIC and SmartSheet. 
 
3 new Columns added are -
 1. Expenditure Type
 2. Expenditure Comment
 3. PA Period
 
Modifications to Integrations are based on mock files provided by Oracle delivery team.
In actual testing, the mock files should be replaced with actual program output generated by the custom EBS process.
 
As part of EBS Program changes 
 
  • EBS Monthly Actuals Report To Smartsheet 
    • Expenditure Type
  • EBS Expenditure Detail Report To Smartsheet
    • Expenditure Type
    •  Expenditure Comment
    • PA Period
  • EBS Financial Detail Report To Smartsheet
    • Expenditure Type
When EBS process places the file on the FTP server -
/EBS_share/CEIEBS/data/cei_oic_out/OIC/Smartsheet/Outbound folder-

Feature.Name: Smartsheet Integration Enhancement

CustomFields.Name: Date When Moved to Make Ready
Date When Moved to In Progress
Acceptance Criteria
CustomFields.Value:
When EBS process places the file on the FTP server -
/EBS_share/CEIEBS/data/cei_oic_out/OIC/Smartsheet/Outbound folder-
 
1. Each of the OIC Integration mentioned  above should read the CSV file with out errors
2. Modified Integration should call Smartsheet API to add rows including newly added columns.
3. Make sure EBS Audit logs is populating newly added columns - RESP_CODE,RESP_MSG & MSG_SOURCE 
4. Ensure the new additions don't impact existing functionality like -
  • Process of creating log entry, initialize global variables, connecting to EBS to query data so forth
  • Archive File with timestamp to Archive Directory
  • OIC audits the final data to the audit tables
  • Error Handling 
5. Update the documents with new changes after successful unit testing

CustomFields.Value:

Items.Name: REQ1347206 RNV Create New Concurrent Program Production Readiness
Items.Description:
As a:  Accountant
I want: A new concurrent program in Oracle EBS that generates a report summarizing AP and PO accrual data by Purchase Order number.So that: I can create more accurate and timely write-offs.

Feature.Name: REQ1347260 - FEATURE#62452 - RNV Analysis View of Cox AP and PO Accrual Reconciliation Report

CustomFields.Name: Date When Moved to Make Ready
Date When Moved to In Progress
Acceptance Criteria
CustomFields.Value:
Acceptance Criteria:
Test new concurrent program named CCI AP and PO Accrual Reconciliation Report by PO
The report will use the existing data source of the Cox AP and PO Accrual Reconciliation Report
The new report will contain these fields only.
 
Report fields

PO Number
PO Order Date
PO Approved Amount
PO Amount Received
PO Amount Invoiced
Write Off Amount
RNV Balance (Received-Invoiced-Write Off)
Age in Days
Vendor Name
PO Charge Account
Inventory Org
 
The report output must be exportable to excel in the same format as the original.
 
The report layout should be clear and easy to read with the appropriate column headings and formatting matching the existing report
 
The report is accessible from the same responsibilities as the existing report Cox AP and PO Accrual Reconciliation Report. 

Responsibilities 
•    CCI AP Super User – COR 
•    CCI AP Corporate – COR 
•    CCI PO SuperUser - COR 
•    CCI Cost Management – SLA 
 
The new report should complete withing 10 minutes
 
The program/query should be thoroughly tested to ensure accurate data retrieval. Query results are to be validated using the existing Cox AP and PO Reconciliation Report..
 
Change Number:TBD Can't create new change due to Service Now upgrade.
 
Tester: Allen Dyment
 
 
Thes report is only for the CCI Division

Package Name: 

File Naming Convention:
